fe.%20To%20keep%20alive%20the%20memory%20of%20their%20work%20is%20to%20remember%20what%20it%20means%20to%20preserve%20our%20wildlife.%20%3Cem%3E(Above%20images%20of%20Kailash%20Sankhala%2C%20J%20Vijaya%20%26amp%3B%20Rinchen%20Wangchuk)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Rinchen%20Wangchuk%3A%20What%20it%20means%20to%20co-exist%20with%20snow%20leopards%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20having%20a%20famous%20father%20in%20Colonel%20Chewang%20Rinchen%2C%20a%20decorated%20Ladakhi%20soldier%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F246169%2Fladakh-snow-leopard-conservancy-india-trust-saviours-rinchen-wangchuk-tsewang-namgail-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERinchen%20Wangchuk%3C%2Fa%3E%20forged%20his%20own%20path.%20As%20a%20wildlife%20researcher%20from%20Ladakh%2C%20he%20framed%20a%20question%20that%20would%20address%20the%20fundamental%20challenge%20of%20snow%20leopard%20conservation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20do%20you%20reconcile%20the%20notion%20of%20snow%20leopard%20conservation%20with%20the%20needs%20of%20local%20communities%20who%20lose%20their%20livestock%2C%20particularly%20sheep%20and%20goats%2C%20to%20these%20elusive%20creatures%3F%20To%20answer%20this%20question%2C%20he%20established%20the%20Snow%20Leopard%20Conservancy-India%20Trust%20(SLC-IT)%20in%202000%20to%20promote%20local%20efforts%20towards%20community-based%20conservation%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20taking%20a%20variety%20of%20steps%20to%20help%20local%20farmers%20and%20nomads%20protect%20their%20livestock%20from%20snow%20leopards%2C%20thus%20preventing%20man-animal%20conflicts%2C%20he%20also%20pioneered%20one%20of%20the%20earliest%20models%20of%20eco-tourism%20with%20conservation-linked%20homestays%20located%20in%20critical%20snow%20leopard%20habitats%20and%20along%20popular%20trekking%20routes.%20These%20successful%20models%20of%20community-based%20tourism%20in%20the%20Hemis%20National%20Park%2C%20the%20Sham%20region%2C%20and%20Zanskar%20still%20stand%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20tragically%20passed%20away%20at%20the%20age%20of%20just%2042%20in%202011%20due%20to%20a%20deteriorating%20neurological%20condition%20but%20not%20before%20leaving%20behind%20a%20stellar%20legacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Fateh%20Singh%20Rathore%3A%20The%20forest%20officer%20who%20showed%20India%20how%20to%20protect%20tigers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKnown%20for%20his%20trademark%20long%20handlebar%20moustache%2C%20olive-coloured%20safari%20hat%20and%20dashing%20dark%20glasses%2C%20the%20late%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F234711%2Fhow-does-india-protect-tigers-fateh-singh-rathore-ranthambhore-national-park-rajasthan-india-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFateh%20Singh%20Rathore%3C%2Fa%3E%20remains%20the%20principal%20architect%20behind%20the%20success%20story%20that%20is%20the%20Ranthambhore%20National%20Park.%20As%20a%20ranger%2C%20warden%2C%20and%20field%20director%20at%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20best-known%20tiger%20preserves%2C%20Fateh%E2%80%99s%20work%20emphasised%20three%20things%20%E2%80%94%20natural%20regeneration%20of%20the%20habitat%2C%20constant%20engagement%20with%20local%20communities%20living%20in%20its%20vicinity%20that%20went%20way%20beyond%20consultations%2C%20and%20an%20abiding%20love%20for%20the%20creatures%20who%20inhabited%20this%20forest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20became%20the%20blueprint%20for%20what%20a%20successful%20tiger%20conservation%20strategy%20looks%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F05103523%2FFateh_Singh_Rathore_2008-500x693.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fateh%20Singh%20Rathore%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-234723%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22693%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EFateh%20Singh%20Rathore%20(Image%20courtesy%20Wikimedia%20Commons)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFateh%E2%80%99s%20approach%20to%20conservation%20was%20marked%20by%20his%20incredible%20knowledge%20of%20the%20terrain%20inside%20Ranthambore%E2%80%99s%20core%20area%20and%20the%20depth%20of%20his%20engagement%20with%20the%20local%20community%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it%20was%20relocating%2016%20villages%20inhabited%20in%20the%20core%20area%20of%20the%20National%20Park%20and%20ensuring%20that%20the%20village%20economy%20thrived%20despite%20this%20resettlement%20and%20a%20crackdown%20on%20poaching.%20He%20nearly%20died%20for%20his%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20as%20a%20forest%20officer%2C%20his%20loyalties%20only%20lay%20with%20the%20forests%20and%20not%20politicians%20or%20superior%20officers%20%E2%80%94%20a%20feature%20of%20his%20work%20that%20would%20come%20at%20a%20great%20personal%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Jamal%20Ara%3A%20The%20first%20%E2%80%98Birdwoman%E2%80%99%20of%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20era%20when%20the%20field%20of%20ornithology%20was%20dominated%20by%20men%2C%20Jamal%20Ara%20stood%20out%20as%20a%20pioneer.%20It%20was%20the%20legendary%20ornithologist%20Salim%20Ali%20who%20called%20her%20the%20first%20%E2%80%98Birdwoman%E2%80%99%20of%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20present-day%20Jharkhand%2C%20her%20work%20on%20the%20ornithology%20of%20the%20Chota%20Nagpur%20plateau%20%E2%80%9Cremains%20the%20only%20comprehensive%20study%20of%20birds%20in%20the%20region%20till%20date%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20an%20essay%20by%20wildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi%20titled%20%3Cem%3EThe%20First%20Lady%20of%20Indian%20Ornithology%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20published%20in%20a%20recent%20collection%20of%20essays%20titled%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FWOMEN-WILD-Brilliant-Wildlife-Biologists%2Fdp%2F9353451817%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWomen%20in%20the%20Wild%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3Eedited%20by%20Anita%20Mani.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20only%20studying%20till%20Class%2010%2C%20she%20was%20a%20prolific%20writer%20on%20the%20subject%20of%20birds.%20According%20to%20Kazmi%2C%20from%201949%20to%201988%2C%20she%20contributed%20to%20more%20than%2060%20papers%20and%20published%20articles%20to%20journals%20including%20the%20Bombay%20Natural%20History%20Society%20and%20Bengal%20Natural%20History%20Society%2C%20and%20the%20Newsletter%20for%20Birdwatchers%2C%20a%20publication%20read%20by%20amateur%20and%20professional%20ornithologists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20more%2C%20she%20also%20wrote%20a%20small%20booklet%20for%20children%20titled%20%3Cem%3EWatching%20Birds%20%3C%2Fem%3Epublished%20by%20the%20National%20Book%20Trust%20(NBT).%20The%20book%20is%20currently%20in%20its%2013th%20edition%20and%20it%20continues%20to%20educate%20children%20on%20the%20birds%20of%20India%20in%20multiple%20languages%20till%20this%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20her%20prolific%20writing%2C%20she%20also%20raised%20awareness%20among%20the%20masses%20through%20her%20programmes%20in%20All%20India%20Radio%20(AIR)%20and%20also%20dabbled%20in%20journalism%20for%20mainstream%20publication.%20%E2%80%9CMore%20importantly%2C%20in%20those%20days%2C%20she%20was%20the%20only%20spokesperson%20for%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20imperilled%20wilderness%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20went%20beyond%20just%20advocating%20for%20birds%2C%20according%20to%20Raza.%20Her%20prescriptions%20and%20recommendations%20would%20lay%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20groundwork%20for%20modern%20conservation%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Kailash%20Sankhala%3A%20The%20unsung%20hero%20who%20changed%20the%20destiny%20of%20tigers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F223419%2Fpadma-shri-kailash-sankhala-project-tiger-kanha-sariska-india-unsung-hero-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKailash%20Sankhala%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20first%20director%20of%20Project%20Tiger%2C%20played%20a%20fundamental%20role%20in%20turning%20the%20tide%20for%20wildlife%20conservation%20in%20India%2C%20particularly%20of%20tigers.%20A%20pioneering%20field%20officer%2C%20he%20did%20real%20field%20research%20work%20to%20understand%20the%20secretive%20lives%20of%20tigers%20from%20their%20behaviour%2C%20population%20dynamics%20to%20daily%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20all%20this%20work%20was%20triggered%20by%20an%20incident%20in%20the%20early%201950s%20when%20he%20killed%20a%20tiger.%20Riddled%20by%20guilt%2C%20it%20transformed%20him%20from%20a%20forest%20officer%20just%20issuing%20hunting%20permits%20to%20spending%20the%20remainder%20of%20his%20life%20protecting%20the%20tiger%20and%20its%20habitat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FKaialsh-Sankhala-2-500x628.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kailash%20Sankhala%20(Source%3A%20Amit%20Sankhala)%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FKaialsh-Sankhala-2-500x628.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FKaialsh-Sankhala-2-239x300.jpeg%20239w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FKaialsh-Sankhala-2-768x965.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FKaialsh-Sankhala-2-1223x1536.jpeg%201223w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FKaialsh-Sankhala-2-1631x2048.jpeg%201631w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FKaialsh-Sankhala-2-scaled.jpeg%202038w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-223426%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EKailash%20Sankhala%20(Source%3A%20Amit%20Sankhala)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20gathering%20public%20support%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20tiger%20conservation%20in%20the%20national%20and%20international%20media%2C%20he%20first%20persuaded%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20to%20ban%20the%20export%20of%20tiger%2C%20leopard%2C%20and%20panther%20skins%20or%20the%20products%20made%20from%20them%20in%201970%20and%20ban%20the%20hunting%20of%20tigers%20altogether%20in%201972.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20later%20in%20April%201973%2C%20prime%20minister%20Gandhi%20established%20Project%20Tiger%20to%20%E2%80%9Cprotect%20and%20restore%20natural%20habitats%20of%20tigers%20and%20to%20track%20and%20protect%20the%20remaining%20wild%20tigers%20in%20India%E2%80%9D%20and%20handpicked%20Sankhala%20as%20its%20first%20director.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20S%20P%20Shahi%3A%20The%20guardian%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20wolves%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahuadanr%20Wolf%20Sanctuary%20in%20Jharkhand%20%E2%80%94%20the%20only%20sanctuary%20in%20India%20dedicated%20to%20wolf%20preservation%20%E2%80%94%20owes%20its%20existence%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F300043%2Fforgotten-forest-officer-sp-shahi-behind-indias-only-wolf-sanctuary-mahuadanr-jharkhand%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ES%20P%20Shahi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20pioneering%20conservationist%20and%20forest%20officer.%20Back%20in%20the%201960s%2C%20he%20paid%20close%20attention%20to%20how%20wolves%20were%20hurtling%20towards%20extinction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi%20noted%20how%20unlike%20most%20forest%20officers%20of%20his%20era%2C%20Shahi%20recognised%20the%20importance%20of%20what%20we%20now%20call%20%E2%80%98Open%20Natural%20Ecosystems%E2%80%99%20for%20wolves.%20These%20ecosystems%20consist%20of%20a%20range%20of%20non-forested%20habitats%20from%20savanna%20grasslands%20to%20deserts%2C%20which%20host%20a%20high%20density%20of%20%E2%80%9Clarge%20mammalian%20fauna%E2%80%9D.%20What%E2%80%99s%20particularly%20interesting%20about%20these%20ecosystems%20is%20that%20unlike%20wildlife%20sanctuaries%20and%20other%20protected%20areas%20where%20limits%20are%20set%20on%20human%20habitation%2C%20they%20support%20the%20lives%20and%20livelihoods%20of%20pastoralists%20and%20their%20livestock.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22SP%20Shahi%20%26amp%3B%20the%20Indian%20grey%20wolf%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-300065%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESP%20Shahi%20%26amp%3B%20the%20Indian%20grey%20wolf%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20like%20Fateh%20Singh%20Rathore%2C%20Shahi%20also%20understood%20the%20role%20of%20local%20communities%20(in%20this%20case%20pastoralists)%20in%20facilitating%20conservation.%20Beyond%20wolves%2C%20Shahi%E2%80%99s%20work%20in%20Palamau%20and%20his%20meticulous%20documentation%20of%20its%20wildlife%20was%20a%20very%20key%20reason%20that%20this%20forest%20was%20declared%20as%20tiger%20reserves%20in%201973%2C%20according%20to%20P%20K%20Sen%2C%20former%20director%20of%20Project%20Tiger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20J%20Vijaya%3A%20The%20defender%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20turtles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%2018%20April%201987%2C%20the%20bodily%20remains%20of%20J%20Vijaya%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20first%20female%20herpetologist%20and%20turtle%20field%20biologist%2C%20were%20found%20in%20Guindy%20National%20Park%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20Only%2028%2C%20the%20cause%20of%20her%20death%20remains%20unknown%20to%20this%20day%20but%20what%20remains%20undeniable%20is%20the%20legacy%20she%20left%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarting%20off%20as%20a%20volunteer%20at%20Madras%20Snake%20Park%20in%201975%20as%20a%20college%20student%2C%20Vijaya%20(known%20to%20her%20friends%20as%20%E2%80%98Viji%E2%80%99)%20would%20go%20on%20to%20not%20only%20become%20one%20of%20the%20foremost%20researchers%20of%20turtles%20but%20also%20play%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20its%20conservation.%20To%20understand%20the%20scope%20of%20turtle%20trade%20and%20the%20exploitation%20it%20entailed%2C%20she%20would%20travel%20the%20length%20and%20breadth%20of%20this%20country%20from%20the%20%E2%80%98badlands%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20Chambal%20(ravines)%20to%20the%20meat%20markets%20of%20Kolkata.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20tribute%20penned%20by%20freelance%20journalist%20Janaki%20Lenin%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fecologise.in%2F2017%2F04%2F18%2Ftribute-viji-turtle-girl%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEcologise%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20black%20and%20white%20pictures%20she%20took%20of%20the%20gory%20Ridley%20sea%20turtle%20slaughter%20on%20Digha%20beach%20and%20in%20the%20meat%20markets%20of%20Calcutta%2C%20shook%20the%20public%20when%20India%20Today%20magazine%20ran%20them%20in%20the%20early%201980s.%20This%20was%20the%20first%20media%20expose%20ever%20done%20on%20the%20free-for-all%20trade%20in%20sea%20turtles%20and%20highlights%20the%20difference%20one%20individual%20can%20make%20for%20conservation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20her%20expose%2C%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20immediately%20took%20action%20against%20the%20exploitation%20of%20sea%20turtles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20Anne%20Wright%3A%20India%E2%80%99s%20adopted%20daughter%20and%20pioneer%20of%20wildlife%20conservation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%204%20October%2C%202023%2C%20India%20mourned%20the%20loss%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F333222%2Fanne-wright-conservationist-wildlife-protection-act-reserves-project-tiger-legacy-raza-kazmi%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnne%20Wright%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20pioneering%20conservationist%20who%20dedicated%20over%20five%20decades%20to%20protecting%20India%E2%80%99s%20wildlife.%20This%20daughter%20of%20a%20British%20civil%20servant%20decided%20to%20adopt%20India%20as%20%E2%80%98her%20country%E2%80%99%20and%20worked%20tirelessly%20to%20protect%20its%20fauna.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnne%20was%20a%20true%20changemaker%2C%20breaking%20gender%20barriers%20in%20wildlife%20conservation%2C%20playing%20a%20key%20role%20in%20drafting%20the%20Wildlife%20(Protection)%20Act%20of%201972%2C%20and%20driving%20the%20creation%20of%20numerous%20Protected%20Areas%2C%20including%20Palamau%20Tiger%20Reserve%20and%20Dalma%20Wildlife%20Sanctuary.%20She%20worked%20closely%20with%20local%20communities%20and%20bureaucracies%20to%20make%20lasting%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Late%20Anne%20Wright%20receiving%20an%20award%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-333245%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ELate%20Anne%20Wright%20receiving%20an%20award%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20working%20towards%20these%20critical%20causes%2C%20in%201970%2C%20she%20also%20wrote%20an%20article%20published%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Statesman%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20describes%20in%20harrowing%20detail%20the%20illegal%20sale%20of%20tiger%20and%20leopard%20skins%20in%20Kolkata.%20The%20article%20was%20republished%20in%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20(NYT)%2C%20causing%20a%20global%20storm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20wildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20article%20was%20debated%20heavily%20in%20the%20Indian%20Parliament%2C%20and%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20an%20exaggeration%20to%20say%20that%20this%20article%2C%20along%20with%20the%20damning%20photographs%20on%20the%20sc